# Drugs Bind to Neurotransmitter Transporters (22)


**3 classes of proteins transport ions across membranes**
* Figure 11.4 Passive and Active Transport Compared is from a section of Chapter 11 of Alberts et. al. Molecular Biology of the Cell   
[Active Transport Is Mediated by Carrier Proteins Coupled to an Energy Source.](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/?term=11.4%20%20passive%20and%20active%20transport%20compared%20AND%20mboc4%5Bbook%5D)
* Alberts B, Johnson A, Lewis J, et al. Molecular Biology of the Cell. 4th edition.
New York: Garland Science; 2002.



**Dopamine transporter (DAT) knockout mice experiment**

*[Mechanisms of Amphetamine Action Revealed in Mice Lacking the Dopamine Transporter](http://www.jneurosci.org/content/18/6/1979.full.pdf) article is open-access   
Jones SR, Gainetdinov RR, Wightman RM, Caron MG. Mechanisms of amphetamine action revealed in mice lacking the dopamine transporter. J Neurosci. 1998 Mar 15;18(6):1979-86.
* The article is publicly available from the Journal of Neuroscience
* from [Dr Sara R. Jones lab](http://www.wakehealth.edu/PhysPharm/Faculty/Sara-R-Jones-PhD.htm), which conducts research measuring neurotransmitters in animal models of drug and alcohol abuse at Wake Forest University.
 

