# Neurotransmitter Transporters as Molecules (23)

**“Alternating Access” Model for ion-coupled transporters**
* Figure 11.9 Three Types of Carrier-Mediated Transport is from a section of Chapter 11 of Alberts et. al. Molecular Biology of the Cell   
[Active Transport Can Be Driven by Ion Gradients.](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/?term=Three%20Types%20of%20Carrier-Mediated%20Transport%20AND%20mboc4%5Bbook%5D)
* Alberts B, Johnson A, Lewis J, et al. Molecular Biology of the Cell. 4th edition.
New York: Garland Science; 2002.

**SSRIs bind tightly to, and stabilize, intermediate state(s) of the serotonin transporter. A Dynamic, Low-Resolution Model**
[Cao et al., J Neurosci 1997](http://www.jneurosci.org/content/17/7/2257.full.pdf)article is open-access [PubMed Abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9065487)
* Cao Y, Mager S, Lester HA. H+ permeation and pH regulation at a mammalian serotonin transporter. J Neurosci. 1997 Apr 1;17(7):2257-66. PubMed PMID: 9065487.
* [from Professor Lester's Lab](http://www.its.caltech.edu/~halweb/)

**Brain of GABA Transporter-GFP ‘Knock-in” Mouse**
*[Chiu et al. GABA Transporter–GFP Counted in Knock-In Mice](http://www.jneurosci.org/content/22/23/10251.full.pdf) article is open-access [PubMed Abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12451126)
* from Professor Lester's Lab
*Chiu CS, Jensen K, Sokolova I, Wang D, Li M, Deshpande P, Davidson N, Mody I, Quick MW, Quake SR, Lester HA. Number, density, and surface/cytoplasmic distribution of GABA transporters at presynaptic structures of knock-in mice carrying GABA transporter subtype 1-green fluorescent protein fusions. J Neurosci. 2002 Dec 1;22(23):10251-66. PubMed PMID: 12451126.
* [from Professor Lester's Lab](http://www.its.caltech.edu/~halweb/)


