# Nicotine addiction
## Components of Addiction.   Animal Models. (27) 

**Chronic nicotine causes tolerance of dopamine release**
*[PubMed Abstract of Rahman, Zhang, Engleman, & Corrigall, 2004](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15453263)
* No open access - you can follow the paywall link to view the figures and associated captions
*Rahman S, Zhang J, Engleman EA, Corrigall WA. Neuroadaptive changes in the
mesoaccumbens dopamine system after chronic nicotine self-administration: a
microdialysis study. Neuroscience. 2004;129(2):415-24. PubMed PMID: 15501598.

## Nicotine Addiction at the circuit and cellular level. 
### “Outside-In” Mechanisms (28)

* Sulzer D. [How addictive drugs disrupt presynaptic dopamine neurotransmission](http://www.cell.com/neuron/retrieve/pii/S0896627311001073). 
Neuron. 2011 Feb 24;69(4):628-49. doi: 10.1016/j.neuron.2011.02.010. 
The article is open-access, click on the full text and it will work (without being a subscriber.)


* You can find it the above paper and several great other review papers [Neuron – Open-Access Reviews on Addiction](http://blogs.plos.org/neuroanthropology/2011/03/08/neuron-open-access-reviews-on-addiction/)  
Follow the links and you will find pdf versions.

