### Upregulation via “Inside-Out” Mechanisms (29)

**Cellular and subcellular specificity of Selective α4* nAChR Upregulation**
* [Nashmi et al J Neurosci 2007](http://www.jneurosci.org/content/27/31/8202.full.pdf) article is open-access [PubMed Abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17670967)
*  Nashmi R, Xiao C, Deshpande P, McKinney S, Grady SR, Whiteaker P, Huang Q, McClure-Begley T, Lindstrom JM, Labarca C, Collins AC, Marks MJ, Lester HA. Chronic nicotine cell specifically upregulates functional alpha 4* nicotinic receptors: basis for both tolerance in midbrain and enhanced long-term potentiation in perforant path. J Neurosci. 2007 Aug 1;27(31):8202-18. PubMed PMID: 17670967.
* [from Professor Lester's Lab](http://www.its.caltech.edu/~halweb/)

* [Xiao et al, J Neurosci 2009](http://www.jneurosci.org/content/29/40/12428.full.pdf) article is open-access [PubMed Abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19812319)
* Xiao C, Nashmi R, McKinney S, Cai H, McIntosh JM, Lester HA. Chronic nicotine selectively enhances alpha4beta2* nicotinic acetylcholine receptors in the nigrostriatal dopamine pathway. J Neurosci. 2009 Oct 7;29(40):12428-39. doi:10.1523/JNEUROSCI.2939-09.2009. PubMed PMID: 19812319; PubMed Central PMCID:PMC2787412.
* [from Professor Lester's Lab](http://www.its.caltech.edu/~halweb/)

**Either activation and/or desensitization can be amplified by upregulation**
*[Miwa et al, Neuron 2011](http://orphanin.caltech.edu/~lester/world/Reprints%20from%20our%20lab/2011/Miwa-neuron-2011.pdf) reprint at Lester Lab [PubMed Abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21482353)
* Miwa JM, Freedman R, Lester HA. Neural systems governed by nicotinic acetylcholine receptors: emerging hypotheses. Neuron. 2011 Apr 14;70(1):20-33. doi: 10.1016/j.neuron.2011.03.014. Review. PubMed PMID: 21482353.
* [from Professor Lester's Lab](http://www.its.caltech.edu/~halweb/)

**“Inside-out” action leads nicotine to upregulate α4β2 nicotinic receptors**
*[PubMed Abstract of Sallette et al, Neuron 2005](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15944128) Open access - follow link and then go to full text
* Sallette J, Pons S, Devillers-Thiery A, Soudant M, Prado de Carvalho L, Changeux JP, Corringer PJ. Nicotine upregulates its own receptors through enhanced intracellular maturation. Neuron. 2005 May 19;46(4):595-607. PubMed PMID: 15944128.

* [Kuryatov et al., Mol. Pharm. 2005](http://molpharm.aspetjournals.org/content/68/6/1839.long) Open access [PubMed Abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16183856)
* Kuryatov A, Luo J, Cooper J, Lindstrom J. Nicotine acts as a pharmacological chaperone to up-regulate human alpha4beta2 acetylcholine receptors. Mol Pharmacol. 2005 Dec;68(6):1839-51. Epub 2005 Sep 23. PubMed PMID: 16183856.

**Two possible results of nicotine-nAChR binding in the endoplasmic reticulum**  

* [RIC-3: a nicotinic acetylcholine receptor chaperone](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2268041/)
* An article I found about nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR ) chaperones while searching for other references. I found it amazing that a type of nAChR  is similar in the nematode <i>C. elegans</i> as well as insects and mammals.
* Millar, N. S. (2008), RIC-3: a nicotinic acetylcholine receptor chaperone. British Journal of Pharmacology, 153: S177–S183. doi: 10.1038/sj.bjp.0707661  

