## Recent Genetic Data (30)

* The Saccone et al. study was a two-stage effort, the first stage did the genotyping of the single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs), while the second stage SNPs for individual genotyping were selected.

**Genome-Wide Association Scans (GWAS) identify single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) affecting nicotine addiction** 
* [Stage 1 Saccone et al, Hum. Mol. Gen., 2007](http://hmg.oxfordjournals.org/content/16/1/24.full.pdf)Open access [PubMed Abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17158188)
* Bierut LJ, Madden PA, Breslau N, Johnson EO, Hatsukami D, Pomerleau OF, Swan GE, Rutter J, Bertelsen S, Fox L, Fugman D, Goate AM, Hinrichs AL, Konvicka K, Martin NG, Montgomery GW, Saccone NL, Saccone SF, Wang JC, Chase GA, Rice JP, Ballinger DG. Novel genes identified in a high-density genome wide association study for nicotine dependence. Hum Mol Genet. 2007 Jan 1;16(1):24-35. Epub 2006 Dec 7. PubMed PMID: 17158188; PubMed Central PMCID: PMC2278047.

**Candidate gene approach identifies a nicotine addiction-related SNP in the coding region of the nicotinic receptor α5 subunit**

* [Stage 2 Saccone et al, Hum. Mol. Gen., 2007](http://hmg.oxfordjournals.org/content/16/1/36.full.pdf)Open access [PubMed Abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17135278)
* Saccone SF, Hinrichs AL, Saccone NL, Chase GA, Konvicka K, Madden PA, Breslau N, Johnson EO, Hatsukami D, Pomerleau O, Swan GE, Goate AM, Rutter J, Bertelsen S, Fox L, Fugman D, Martin NG, Montgomery GW, Wang JC, Ballinger DG, Rice JP, Bierut LJ. Cholinergic nicotinic receptor genes implicated in a nicotine dependence association study targeting 348 candidate genes with 3713 SNPs. Hum Mol Genet. 2007 Jan 1;16(1):36-49. Epub 2006 Nov 29. PubMed PMID: 17135278; PubMed Central PMCID: PMC2270437.

